    \rulename{app-rec} & \movesto & |apply^(n => (if n == 0 then 0 else apply^(def a in a == sub^(n, 1); (rec f F, a))), 0)| \\
    \rulename{app-lam} & \movesto & |def t in t == 0; if t == 0 then 0 else apply^(def a in a == sub^(t, 1); (rec f F, a))| \\
    \rulename{bind} & \movesto & |def t:=0 in 0; if t == 0 then 0 else apply^(def a in a == sub^(t, 1); (rec f F, a))| \\
    \rulename{seq} & \movesto & |def t:=0 in if t == 0 then 0 else apply^(def a in a == sub^(t, 1); (rec f F, a))| \\
    \rulename{subst} & \movesto & |def t:=0 in if 0 == 0 then 0 else apply^(def a in a == sub^(0, 1); (rec f F, a))| \\
    \rulename{top-def} & \movesto & |if 0 == 0 then 0 else apply^(def a in a == sub^(0, 1); (rec f F, a))| \\
    \rulename{ucon} & \movesto & |if 0 then 0 else apply^(def a in a == sub^(0, 1); (rec f F, a))| \\
    \rulename{if-true} & \movesto & |0| \\
  \end{array}$$
\end{example}
To save space we have used the abbreviation |F| for the expression \newline
|(n => (if n == 0 then 0 else apply^(def a in a == sub^(n, 1); (f, a))))|.

